<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2018-04-11</DATELINE><TITLE>Turning Up Your Nose for a Flaviviral Encephalitis Cure</TITLE><BODY>siRNA approaches have demonstrated promise in treating viral infections in animal models, but poor delivery limits clinical application. In this issue of Cell Host & Microbe, Beloor et al. (2018) report that nose-to-brain delivery of viral-targeted siRNA cures mice from West Nile virus encephalitis, with potential implications for human infection.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>